-----------------------------------------
Cloud
-----------------------------------------
access your virtual resource over network is called cloud computing.
org ==> private cloud computing
public ==> public cloud computing, AWS, Azure

more than 90% of organizatiosn using cloud computing

agility, elasticity, costy saving (Pay as you use), can go global in mins

Type od cloud computing ==> Iaas (infrastructure as a Service), Paas (platform aas a service), Saas (s/w as a service)
AWS Free Tier account ==> set up an account, setup IAM user

The AWS Cloud spans 123 Availability Zones within 39 Geographic Regions

https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regions_az/

EC2 Servcie (Elastic Compute Cloud):
> provides webservices for provisioning, managing, deprovisioning virtual servers on amazon cloud
> ease in scaling up/down
> pay only for what you use
> can be integrated into several other services

pricing ==> on Demand(pay per hr), Reserved (1 to 3 yrs), SPot (unused ec2 resources u can bid with huge discount), dedicated hosts (physical server dedicated for you very expensive)
Component in EC2:
AMI (amazon m/c images like vargrant boxes) provided info req'd to launch an isntancei.e. virtual server in the cloud
Instace type the instance type u specify when you lauch determines the h/w of the host computer used for your instance 
EBS (amazon Elastic Block Store amazon provides flexible, cost effective and easy-to-use data storage options for yopur instances) its virtual hard disk
tags good for filtering and billing
security group - firewall for inbound and outbound traffic
Key pair - to login to instance , we use this to create pwd

-----------------------------------------
Create EC2 instance
-----------------------------------------

Each region has atleast 2 zone... zone are teh actual Physical centers

Choose AMI , select isnatnce type, configure the instance (n/w, permission, scripts to execute), adding storage, tags (key value pars..etc) , configure security group, and review 

gather requirement (OS; size- RAM, cpu,n/w; Storage size; project; services/apps running - SSH, http, mysql etc;environment - dev,QA,staging,pre-prod, Prod; Login User - for trackign and tagging)
create keypair 
create security group
launch instance

ssh -i <keyfile .pem> user@<public ip>

private IP is static for instance , public IP is everytime dynamacally given each time the instace is repowered 
elastic IP (public static IP) unique ip address alloted to ur instance they are not for free
private , public Ip and security group are associated to n/w interface
each instance can have one or more n/w interface

