-----------------------------------------
SSM  & Cloud Shell Intro
-----------------------------------------
AWS Sytems Manager - u cna manage many notes at scale
U can run your command on one note or multiple notes at a time
goto IAM service > Roles > create role
AWS Service, Usecase : EC2, Select Policy select 'AmazonSSmManagedInstanceCore' , give role name and create role
attach this role to instance.ACTIONS> SECURITY>MODIFY IAM ROLE and select ur role and update
Amazon SSM > session manager and click on start session
Select Your instance and next 'Start your session' in new tab you will get a session where u can perform all actions on the instance without ssh or login

To run command on one or multi notes

'Run Command' > choose options and run

AWS clopud shell (with user account permissions we cna do with out aws cli)

